      "content": "thanks for these. they're a good start, but they feel a bit surface-level for a high-level policy debate. my kids need to go deeper than just \"sovereignty\" and \"resources.\" can you expand on the economic argument? specifically, how do proponents frame the relationship between strict enforcement and the protection of domestic labor markets and wage stability? give me the most sophisticated version of that logic.",
